description.et:
Ethnopolitical regime country case study. 
The ethnopolitical regime country case study will be assessed according to how well
a)	the report summarizes key information about the particular ethnopolitical situation and resulting constellations in the assigned country; 
b)	the report critically reflects on the efficacy and effects of the established mode of ethnic conflict management/regulation in the country; 
c)	the report remains within the page limits and relies on decent academic sources (reliable/verifiable internet sources, academic articles etc.) that are properly referenced;
d)	the report is properly formatted and designed in order to ease the reading.
